Scientific Revolution

Chemical revolution
- Antoine Lavoisier [Combustion, Acid–base reaction]
- Humphry Davy: Electrolysis, Potassium, Sodium, Calcium, Magnesium, Silicon, Aluminium
- John Dalton [Atomic theory]
- Robert Boyle [Boyle's law]

William Herschel: Uranus (1781)
Urbain Le Verrier: Neptune (1846)

Alexander Fleming, Penicilin (1928)
Robert Koch: Anthrax, Tuberculosis, Cholera
Joseph Lister: Antiseptic surgery

Sundial / Shadow clock
