Genetics
- Gregor Mendel [Inheritance, Dominance] (1856-1865)
- Thomas Hunt Morgan: Genes on chromosomes (1910) + Drosophila melanogaster (1910)
- James Watson, Francis Crick [The double helix] (1953)
- Walter Fiers: Gene sequence (1972)
- Human genome (2003)

Copernican Revolution (16th-17th century)
- Giordano Bruno [Cosmic pluralism: stars are suns, life on other planets]
- Nicolaus Copernicus [Heliocentrism]
- Johannes Kepler [Laws of planetary motion]
- Galileo Galilei: Telescope (1609) + Jupiter's moons, Saturn's rings, Sunspots (1610)

Venetian Patent Statute (1474)

Robert Hooke: Cell (1665)
Theodor Schwann + Matthias Jakob Schleiden: Cell theory (1839)
- All living organisms are composed of one or more cells
- The cell is the most basic unit of life
Rudolf Virchow: Cell theory (1855)
- All cells arise only from pre-existing cells

