Anti-ship glide bomb (1943): Fritz X, WWII, Nazi Germany
Cruise missile: V1, WWII, Nazi Germany
Ballistic missile: V2, WWII, Nazi Germany
Laser-guided bomb (1960s): Paveway, Vietnam War, USA

Piltdown Man (1912): fossil fraud of human-ape missing link

Oppau Explosion (1921): ammonium sulfate and nitrate explosion at BASF plant, Germany
- destroyed glass windows of Worms Cathedral
Bhopal Disaster (1984): toxic gas leak at pesticide plant, India
Evangelos Florakis Naval Base explosion (2011): ammunition and explosives, Cyprus
- destroyed Vasilikos Power Station, caused blackouts
Notre Dame Fire (2019): destroyed wooden roof
Beirut Explosion (2020): ammonium nitrate explosion at port

Atomic Age
- Atomic bomb: Manhattan project, Robert Oppenheimer, Trinity, Los Alamos (1945)
- Hydrogen bomb: Edward Teller (1952)
- Nuclear power plant (1954): core meltdown, Red Forest
- Chernobyl disaster (1986)
- Fukushima disaster (2011): tsunami

Space exploration
- Konstantin Tsiolkovsky: rocket scientist, astronautic theory
- V-2 rocket, guided ballistic missile (Wernher von Braun) [1944]
- Artificial sattelite (Sputnik, Laika) [1957]
- Astronaut, Vostok (Yuri Gagarin) [1961]
- Moon landing, Apollo 11 (Neil Armstrong, Buzz Aldrin) [1969]
- Interstellar (Voyager) [1977]
- Space Shuttle Challenger disaster [1986]: launch
- Hubble Space Telescope [1990]
- Space Shuttle Columbia disaster [2003]: reentry
- James Webb Space Telescope [2022]
- Chang'e Project: China, moon exploration
- Chandrayaan programme: India, moon exploration

Modular space station
- Mir (1996): USSR, continuously inhabited, decommission in 2001
- ISS / International Space Station (2000): continuously inhabited
- Tiangong (2021): China

